So it seems to work fine without local: Took about 10 minutes

`2020/05/10 22:25:47 DEBUG : rclone: Version "v1.51.0-300-g54b16bd0-beta" starting with parameters ["rclone" "rc" "vfs/refresh" "recursive=true" "-vvv" "--timeout" "60m"]
{
	"result": {
		"": "OK"
	}
}
2020/05/10 22:35:26 DEBUG : 4 go routines active`

With local:
`rclone rc vfs/refresh recursive=true -vvv --timeout 60m
2020/05/10 22:37:54 DEBUG : rclone: Version "v1.51.0-300-g54b16bd0-beta" starting with parameters ["rclone" "rc" "vfs/refresh" "recursive=true" "-vvv" "--timeout" "60m"]`

It's still running and I've had it running for about 20m now. So your theory on it not working with local is correct.

@Max-Sum

First of all, thx for the effort :-).

I have also repeated a similar test again and the result is the same (mounted with the beta):

- Only with remote:

```bash
$ time rclone-v1.51.0-301-g10a6a92e-beta-linux-amd64/rclone rc vfs/refresh recursive=true dir=/test
{
        "result": {
                "/test": "OK"
        }
}

real    0m3.679s
user    0m0.027s
sys     0m0.010s
```

- With union (local+remote):

```bash
$ time rclone-v1.51.0-301-g10a6a92e-beta-linux-amd64/rclone rcvfs/refresh recursive=true dir=/test
{
        "result": {
                "/test": "OK"
        }
}

real    0m40.209s
user    0m0.019s
sys     0m0.013s
```
